Shoppers have been left baffled by a bizarre car park - which blocks motorists from parking in spaces after blocking them with BOLLARDS.

Angry customers claim they have been forced to park in a bus stop when visiting Tesco Express in the Hall Green area of Birmingham - after the council decided to block off parking spaces to the local Tesco Express store.

Five of the seven spaces at the store are completely unusable - leaving shoppers stumped. Tesco said it had also registered a complaint with the council.

