'There is one disabled space that can be driven into, but once someone parks there, it blocks all access to any other spaces.

'It's a small store, so people only nip in for a few minutes - but when you come out again, someone's usually blocking you in and it causes complete chaos.

'It's our only local shop, on a very busy road, so it's a nightmare. I don't know how there haven't been more accidents there.'

A Tesco spokesperson said: 'The council made the decision to put the bollards in. We objected at the time and agree with our customers who would like to see the bollards removed.'

